# Tensor Analysis Studio

A rigorous, production-ready tensor algebra framework that unifies symbolic Einstein-notation manipulation and high-performance numeric evaluation, with first-class support for coordinate systems, metrics, covariant derivatives, index gymnastics (raise/lower), and visual tools to inspect tensor flows.

## Features

- **Einstein Notation**: Intuitive index notation for tensor operations with automatic contraction detection
- **Index Management**: Explicit covariant/contravariant index tracking with automatic raise/lower operations
- **Metric Tensors**: Full support for metrics, signatures, and index manipulation
- **Differential Geometry**: Christoffel symbols, covariant derivatives, Lie derivatives
- **Coordinate Systems**: Built-in Cartesian, spherical, cylindrical frames with transformation support
- **Multiple Backends**: NumPy (default), JAX (for autodiff/JIT), CuPy (GPU acceleration)
- **Symbolic Computation**: Optional SymPy integration for symbolic tensor algebra
- **Visualization**: Tensor flow diagrams, field plots, and interactive inspectors
- **Type Safety**: Full type annotations with mypy strict mode

## Installation

```bash
# Basic installation (NumPy only)
pip install tensor-analysis-studio

# With symbolic support
pip install tensor-analysis-studio[symbolic]

# With visualization
pip install tensor-analysis-studio[viz]

# With JAX backend
pip install tensor-analysis-studio[jax]

# Full installation
pip install tensor-analysis-studio[all]
```

## Quick Start

```python
import numpy as np
from tas import Tensor, Index, Metric
from tas.core.einsum_parser import einsum_eval

# Create tensors with explicit indices
A = Tensor(np.random.rand(3, 3), indices=("^i", "_j"))
B = Tensor(np.random.rand(3, 3), indices=("^j", "_k"))

# Einstein notation contraction
C = einsum_eval("A^i_j B^j_k", A=A, B=B)

# Define a metric
g = Metric(np.eye(3), indices=("_i", "_j"))

# Raise/lower indices
A_raised = A.raise_index(metric=g, axis=1)

# Covariant derivative
from tas.core.connections import Connection
from tas.core.diffops import covariant_derivative

conn = Connection.from_metric(g)
grad_A = covariant_derivative(A, conn)
```

## Use Cases

- **General Relativity**: Compute Christoffel symbols, Riemann tensors, Einstein equations
- **Continuum Mechanics**: Stress-energy tensors, elasticity, fluid dynamics
- **Machine Learning**: Advanced tensor operations with index awareness
- **Education**: Interactive visualizations of tensor operations and transformations

## Documentation

Full documentation is available at [tensor-analysis-studio.readthedocs.io](https://tensor-analysis-studio.readthedocs.io)

## Development

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/tensor-analysis-studio.git
cd tensor-analysis-studio

# Install development dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run tests
pytest

# Type checking
mypy tas

# Format code
black tas tests
ruff check tas tests
```

